rComments: Very confusing, wasn't clear about tests or anything. Made assumptions that we a knew what she was talking about. I'm not one to really dislike a class but she really was terrible.

Norma was very unclear about her expectations of her students. She was very confusing and a dry lecturer. Did not provide any powerpoint notes or summaries of what she lectured - it was all her talking in front of the class. The class moved very fast paced & she was very inconsiderate with the HUGE amount of work given and the LACK of resources.

This was a very interesting class. Through the different texts one is able to see the various points of view of the Mexican Revolutionaries. Klahn is a very good professor in the sense that she explains herself and is always open to answer any doubts. She is also a very good listener.
